this one goal in mind,

00:01:03.170 --> 00:01:04.780
to know the meaning of life.

00:01:04.780 --> 00:01:11.310
And then with so much passion
and integrity to himself,

00:01:11.310 --> 00:01:13.020
how he found that goal.

00:01:13.020 --> 00:01:16.150
And then the rest of his life
is a dedication to that goal.

00:01:16.150 --> 00:01:21.290
So that's what brings him
here today for this topic

00:01:21.290 --> 00:01:25.870
on integrity or influence
without affluence,

00:01:25.870 --> 00:01:29.610
the power of integrity
and authenticity.

00:01:29.610 --> 00:01:31.860
So basically the reason
he chose that topic

00:01:31.860 --> 00:01:35.280
is because that's the
essence of his personality.

00:01:35.280 --> 00:01:39.150
I've known him for like 17
years and heard his lectures

00:01:39.150 --> 00:01:40.150
and talks.

00:01:40.150 --> 00:01:42.720
And he's a very humble person.

00:01:42.720 --> 00:01:45.690
And the last thing
I could expect

00:01:45.690 --> 00:01:48.240
is that he would write
a book about himself.

00:01:48.240 --> 00:01:53.150
Why would a monk, who is so
humble, write about himself?

00:01:53.150 --> 00:01:57.990
Normally, people read books as
a ego trip or just to show off.

00:01:57.990 --> 00:02:01.080
But then the reason
he wrote this book is

00:02:01.080 --> 00:02:05.360
to show how one could be
successful if one first

00:02:05.360 --> 00:02:11.280
used one's own calling of the
heart despite all obstacles

00:02:11.280 --> 00:02:13.580
and remain committed
to that goal.

00:02:13.580 --> 00:02:15.810
So that's the real
essence of his being.

00:02:15.810 --> 00:02:18.330
And the book here,
"Journey Home,"

00:02:18.330 --> 00:02:20.852
there's a bunch of
copies available

