00:51:47.740 --> 00:51:49.791
In so many
traditions, especially

00:51:49.791 --> 00:51:51.790
in our own traditions,
it's call Brahma-muhurta.

00:51:59.610 --> 00:52:01.530
It's a very powerful
time of the day

00:52:01.530 --> 00:52:03.980
to make spiritual connections.

00:52:03.980 --> 00:52:07.580
And for focus and concentration
because kind of everybody

00:52:07.580 --> 00:52:08.890
is sleeping.

00:52:08.890 --> 00:52:12.340
And the passions of
the world around us

00:52:12.340 --> 00:52:16.840
haven't really started
filling the environment.

00:52:16.840 --> 00:52:21.920
And because we're just woken up,
our mind and our consciousness

00:52:21.920 --> 00:52:24.620
is kind of like a blank slate.

00:52:24.620 --> 00:52:29.600
And if we fill it with something
wonderful, with divine grace,

00:52:29.600 --> 00:52:31.460
then throughout the
day we can actually

00:52:31.460 --> 00:52:36.540
be energized, empowered,
to share that grace.

00:52:36.540 --> 00:52:41.240
So we begin, we chant
the names of God,

00:52:41.240 --> 00:52:46.350
usually for a couple
hours-- and prayer beads.

00:52:46.350 --> 00:52:49.090
It's a type of meditation.

00:52:49.090 --> 00:52:53.090
The mantra in my tradition
is Hare Krishna Hare Krishna

00:52:53.090 --> 00:52:58.100
Krishna Krishna Hare Hare
Hare Rama Hare Rama Rama Rama.

00:52:58.100 --> 00:53:00.790
We believe that all these
mantras or all these divine

00:53:00.790 --> 00:53:04.980
sounds from all these great
spiritual traditions connect us

00:53:04.980 --> 00:53:08.250
to that divine essence
and that grace within us.

00:53:10.920 --> 00:53:15.720
And when I'm near it,
an ashram, we usually

00:53:15.720 --> 00:53:18.925
have kirtan or
chanting together,

00:53:18.925 --> 00:53:21.050
where, like the
redwood roots, we're

00:53:21.050 --> 00:53:24.900
all united for one purpose,
to try to purify and cleanse

00:53:24.900 --> 00:53:28.790
the world through
Krishna, God's grace.

00:53:28.790 --> 00:53:30.425
And we study
scriptures together.

00:53:35.650 --> 00:53:37.090
Then we take sacred food.

00:53:37.090 --> 00:53:39.360
We're vegetarians.

00:53:39.360 --> 00:53:42.160
And then we go and do our seva.

00:53:42.160 --> 00:53:46.260
My seva is-- I live in
India actually, in Mumbai.

00:53:46.260 --> 00:53:49.140
And we have many projects.

00:53:49.140 --> 00:53:53.710
We have an ashram with
about 150 monks in it.

00:53:53.710 --> 00:53:55.150
And we have the temple.

00:53:55.150 --> 00:53:58.030
And many thousands of
people come every day.

00:53:58.030 --> 00:54:04.610
And we have a congregation
of over 10,000 people.

00:54:04.610 --> 00:54:07.110
And we have a 200-bed hospital.

00:54:07.110 --> 00:54:10.580
And we have an orphanage
and we have a hospice.

00:54:10.580 --> 00:54:13.420
And we have this one
project for feeding children

00:54:13.420 --> 00:54:16.410
in the ghetto schools
in the Bombay area.

00:54:16.410 --> 00:54:22.210
Because the number one reason
for illiteracy is hunger.

00:54:22.210 --> 00:54:25.675
And instead of children going
and working-- child labor

00:54:25.675 --> 00:54:30.600
or begging-- if they get
food, they'll stay in school.

00:54:30.600 --> 00:54:34.250
So we are feeding about
410,000 children a day

00:54:34.250 --> 00:54:37.120
now from our kitchens.

00:54:37.120 --> 00:54:39.390
And we have an
eco-village, where

00:54:39.390 --> 00:54:42.550
we have beautiful
cows and other animals

00:54:42.550 --> 00:54:44.830
that we protect
throughout their lives.

00:54:44.830 --> 00:54:48.220
And we build our buildings
out of the natural earth

00:54:48.220 --> 00:54:51.630
that's around us, in
eco-friendly ways.

00:54:51.630 --> 00:54:54.860
And we have natural
organic sewage refineries.

00:54:54.860 --> 00:54:59.120
So every time you
flush the toilet,

00:54:59.120 --> 00:55:03.840
you're actually investing
a wonderful contribution

00:55:03.840 --> 00:55:05.090
into the community.

00:55:09.970 --> 00:55:12.970
It takes longer than nine
minutes to talk about this.

00:55:12.970 --> 00:55:14.120
But it's quite incredible.

00:55:14.120 --> 00:55:16.960
By gravity and solar power,
you flush the toilet.

00:55:16.960 --> 00:55:18.910
And it goes into a place.

00:55:18.910 --> 00:55:22.210
And then it comes down
through these different herbs,

00:55:22.210 --> 00:55:26.905
and roots, and
stones to filter it.

00:55:26.905 --> 00:55:28.540
And it comes out
crystal-clear water.

00:55:31.666 --> 00:55:33.040
We have thousands
of fruit trees.

00:55:33.040 --> 00:55:35.550
And we grow our
own organic food.

00:55:35.550 --> 00:55:39.800
But interestingly, we had
a yoga group from New York

00:55:39.800 --> 00:55:40.940
just a couple months ago.

00:55:40.940 --> 00:55:42.330
I was there.

00:55:42.330 --> 00:55:44.410
And they looking at the papayas.

00:55:44.410 --> 00:55:46.576
They were about this big.

00:55:46.576 --> 00:55:48.730
And they were eating
the papayas every day.

00:55:48.730 --> 00:55:49.970
They really liked it.

00:55:49.970 --> 00:55:53.630
And then they came up to where
this sewage refinery was.

00:55:53.630 --> 00:55:56.082
And papayas were about this big.

00:55:56.082 --> 00:55:59.690
[LAUGHTER]

00:55:59.690 --> 00:56:08.900
So on one lady yogi, she gave
a new name to our papayas.

00:56:08.900 --> 00:56:16.890
She called them "poopayas."

00:56:16.890 --> 00:56:19.080
So I kind oversee
these projects.

00:56:19.080 --> 00:56:23.160
And I have a lot of meetings
and a lot of counseling.

00:56:23.160 --> 00:56:25.780
We have thousands and
thousands of married couples.

